doc.ContractDescription: WE PROPOSE AN EXPLORATORY EPIC OBSERVATION OF A NEARBY RECYCLED RAY PULSAR RECENTLY DETECTED IN THE RADIO. THOSE FOR WHICH A MULTIWAVELENGTH ANALYSIS HAS BEEN DONE SHOW AN INTRIGUING CONNECTION BETWEEN THE RAY AND X-RAY SPECTRA. IN A MODEST EXPOSURE WE WILL COLLECT ENOUGH COUNTS TO TEST THE PUTATIVE LINK BETWEEN THE RAY AND X-RAY SPECTRA. THE RESULTS WILL ADVANCE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF THE INNER WORKINGS OF THE PULSAR MAGNETOSPHERES, INCLUDING PAIR CASCADES, PARTICLE ACCELERATION, MAGNETOSPHERIC CURRENT DISTRIBUTION, AND RADIATION PROCESSES IN STRONG MAGNETIC FIELDS.
